    "title": "Guided Practice",
    "objective": "Categorize PUWER and the On-Site Guide into statutory and non-statutory classifications.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Scenario: You are checking your tool kit and your reference books. You have the Provision and Use of Work Equipment Regulations (PUWER) and the On-Site Guide.",
      "Step 1: Identify the legal status of PUWER. It is a set of regulations passed by Parliament regarding equipment safety.",
      "Step 2: Identify the legal status of the On-Site Guide. It is a practical handbook published by the IET to help apply the Wiring Regulations.",
      "Step 3: Classify them. Laws are statutory; handbooks and guides are non-statutory."
    ],
    "questionText": "Based on the steps provided, classify PUWER and the On-Site Guide as either statutory or non-statutory.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "PUWER is statutory and the On-Site Guide is non-statutory",
      "PUWER: Statutory; On-Site Guide: Non-statutory"
    ],
    "hint": "Remember: If it's a regulation passed by Parliament, it's statutory. If it's a guide on how to do the job, it's non-statutory."
  },
